   3. Code which inherits Duke classes outside of the Duke libraries does not form a derived work.
   4. Statically linking the Duke libraries into a user application does not make the user application a derived work.

As per the terms of the LGPL, a “derived work” is one for which you have to distribute source code for, so when the clauses above define something as not a derived work, it means you don’t have to distribute source code for it. However, the original Duke source code with all modifications must always be made available.
